## 🔹 1. Problem kya hoti hai?

👉 React me jab parent re-render hota hai
👉 to child bhi re-render ho jata hai 😵

👉 Even jab zarurat nahi hoti

---

## 🔹 2. React.memo (🔥 Re-render control)

👉 Component ko unnecessary re-render se bachata hai

### ✅ Example:

```jsx
import React from "react";

const Child = React.memo(({ name }) => {
  console.log("Child rendered");

  return <h2>{name}</h2>;
});

export default Child;
```

### Parent:

```jsx
import { useState } from "react";
import Child from "./Child";

function App() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <>
      <Child name="Sachin" />

      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>
        {count}
      </button>
    </>
  );
}
```

### 🔥 Result:

👉 Button click pe Parent re-render hoga
👉 BUT Child re-render nahi hoga ✅

### 🤔 Kab use kare?

👉 Jab component heavy ho
👉 Same props repeat ho

---

## 🔹 3. useMemo (🔥 Expensive calculation optimize)

👉 Value ko cache karta hai

### ✅ Example:

```jsx
import { useMemo, useState } from "react";

function App() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  const expensiveCalc = useMemo(() => {
    console.log("Calculating...");
    return count * 2;
  }, [count]);

  return (
    <>
      <h1>{expensiveCalc}</h1>

      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>
        +
      </button>
    </>
  );
}
```

### 🔥 Benefit:

👉 Calculation har render pe nahi chalega
👉 Sirf dependency change pe chalega

---

## 🔹 4. useCallback (🔥 Function memoization)

👉 Function ko re-create hone se bachata hai

### ✅ Example:

```jsx
import { useState, useCallback } from "react";

function App() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
    console.log("Clicked");
  }, []);

  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={handleClick}>Click</button>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>
        {count}
      </button>
    </>
  );
}
```

### 🤔 Kyu use kare?

👉 Jab function child component ko pass karte ho
👉 warna child re-render hota rahega

---

## 🔥 React.memo + useCallback Combo

```jsx
const Child = React.memo(({ onClick }) => {
  console.log("Child rendered");
  return <button onClick={onClick}>Click</button>;
});

const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  console.log("Clicked");
}, []);
```

👉 Perfect optimization combo 💯

---

## 🎯 Kab kya use kare? (🔥 GOLD RULE)

| Tool        | Use                         |
| ----------- | --------------------------- |
| React.memo  | Component re-render control |
| useMemo     | Heavy calculation           |
| useCallback | Function reference stable   |

